# Optional: dedicated Solana mainnet RPC (browser). If unset, the app uses public
# fallbacks (publicnode, Ankr, etc.) in order.
#
# If you see errors like:
#   "API KEY IS NOT ALLOWED TO ACCESS BLOCKCHAIN" (403 / -32052)
# your provider key is valid but not allowed to call JSON-RPC from the dashboard.
# Fix: in Helius / Alchemy / QuickNode, enable "RPC" / "Blockchain" access for that key,
# or create a key type meant for Solana JSON-RPC — not REST-only or analytics-only keys.
#
# Quick workaround: comment out VITE_RPC_URL and restart `npm run dev` so the app skips
# your key for this browser session (we also auto-skip a failing key until you close the tab).
#
# VITE_RPC_URL=https://mainnet.helius-rpc.com/?api-key=YOUR_KEY
#
# Jupiter: Metis (`api.jup.ag`) quote/swap REQUIRES an API key. Legacy v6 (`quote-api.jup.ag`)
# may work without one, but if you see 401 or quotes never load, add a key:
# https://portal.jup.ag/
# VITE_JUPITER_API_KEY=
#
# Same-origin Jupiter proxy (same APIs jup.ag/swap uses — see https://docs.jup.ag/ ):
# - In `npm run dev`, proxy is ON by default (vite.config.js → quote-api + api.jup.ag).
# - Set to false to force direct browser → Jupiter (tests CORS).
# VITE_JUPITER_SAME_ORIGIN=false
#
# Production static hosting has no Vite proxy; set true ONLY if your CDN/nginx rewrites:
#   /__jupiter_quote/* → https://quote-api.jup.ag/*
#   /__jupiter_api/*    → https://api.jup.ag/*
# VITE_JUPITER_SAME_ORIGIN=true

